00:15:16,480 --> 00:15:22,460
2 quadrillion 4 trillion
673 million 274 632.

252
00:15:26,720 --> 00:15:28,015
Can I go?

253
00:15:28,039 --> 00:15:29,553
Yes. Have a good evening.

254
00:15:34,280 --> 00:15:38,274
Hey, stop it!
How restless you are . . .

255
00:15:43,853 --> 00:15:45,861
- Shall we go skating?
- I'm not done yet!

256
00:15:45,886 --> 00:15:48,367
- At this time?
- The experiment is still in progress.

257
00:15:48,392 --> 00:15:50,114
- A very diligent young lady!
- So what?

258
00:15:50,139 --> 00:15:51,958
So should I leave?
- Yes.

259
00:15:56,160 --> 00:15:59,710
Here,
take Atom and come back in an hour.

260
00:16:02,579 --> 00:16:05,385
Pass me the data,
they should be ready.

261
00:16:07,733 --> 00:16:08,801
Was he your boyfriend?

262
00:16:08,825 --> 00:16:11,559
No, boss.
Just a classmate.

263
00:16:11,720 --> 00:16:15,714
Thank you. He is not even a friend.
He is nobody in short.

264
00:16:15,880 --> 00:16:18,375
If you want, go with him,
I can finish by myself.

265
00:16:18,400 --> 00:16:20,693
No, boss.
I'm passionate about this work.

266
00:16:21,200 --> 00:16:25,460
Yes, I'm sure I will be passionate about it....
But I would like to understand...

267
00:16:25,485 --> 00:16:26,619
What?

268
00:16:26,644 --> 00:16:30,055
If you don't mind explaining, it's the
ant thing that I don't understand.

269
00:16:30,080 --> 00:16:33,146
With larger animals,
yes, but with ants....

270
00:16:33,171 --> 00:16:36,678
All right-do you remember my
course on freezing?

271
00:16:36,703 --> 00:16:40,959
You will remember that toads and fish became
frozen and hardened like stones,

272
00:16:41,120 --> 00:16:44,909
But once they warmed up they
resumed life as if nothing had happened.

273
00:16:45,080 --> 00:16:49,836
Ants freeze at zero
absolute kelvin, or -273 degrees,

274
00:16:50,000 --> 00:16:51,726
have revived normally.

275
00:16:51,751 --> 00:16:54,041
Has a person ever been
frozen in a laboratory?

276
00:16:54,065 --> 00:16:55,573
No, no, do you volunteer?

277
00:16:56,579 --> 00:16:59,711
All scientists
dream of freezing life.

278
00:16:59,880 --> 00:17:02,076
My idea is to
replace the cold

279
00:17:02,101 --> 00:17:05,358
with a product that has a similar effect
similar on living cells.

280
00:17:05,520 --> 00:17:08,135
Instead of freezing them, I coagulate them.

281
00:17:08,160 --> 00:17:12,074
So I slow down life at will.

282
00:17:12,186 --> 00:17:16,653
Here is a drop
containing live protozoa.

283
00:17:19,640 --> 00:17:23,832
Here's another one,
where they are all dead.

284
00:17:26,040 --> 00:17:31,606
And here finally, the one where life
Is suspended, thanks to my product.

285
00:17:33,960 --> 00:17:37,128
My N734

286
00:17:37,152 --> 00:17:40,420
Should act in the same way
on ant cells.

287
00:17:41,960 --> 00:17:44,306
I'll take an ant...

288
00:17:53,346 --> 00:17:54,361
But where is it?

289
00:17:54,385 --> 00:17:56,671
That is exactly what I would like to know.

290
00:17:56,840 --> 00:17:59,400
Do you see anything there?

291
00:18:01,640 --> 00:18:02,710
Have you seen it?

292
00:18:05,040 --> 00:18:08,397
Excuse me... That was not my intention.

293
00:18:15,880 --> 00:18:20,001
So? Do they keep
disappear these ants?

294
00:18:20,025 --> 00:18:21,038
Yeah.

295
00:18:21,480 --> 00:18:23,021
Do you suffer so much that you don't eat?

296
00:18:23,045 --> 00:18:25,553
Put yourself in my place.
It's my job.

297
00:18:25,720 --> 00:18:31,255
Look... you are free to
to do whatever you want, but ...

298
00:18:31,279 --> 00:18:33,158
If I were you, I would leave it alone.

299
00:18:33,320 --> 00:18:37,951
Something tells me you are on the
wrong path. Female intuition.

300
00:18:40,560 --> 00:18:43,273
Let's go.
Put on the dress quickly.

301
00:18:43,298 --> 00:18:44,298
Is it that way?

302
00:18:44,323 --> 00:18:47,279
Yes, in your room.
There, in the cardboard boxes.

303
00:18:47,720 --> 00:18:48,825
You know what...?

304
00:18:48,849 --> 00:18:50,030
What?

305
00:18:50,200 --> 00:18:53,113
The Bonjeans have
offered coffee service.

306
00:18:53,280 --> 00:18:56,175
Baroness Edmond has an ice bucket
for ice made of jewels.

307
00:18:56,200 --> 00:18:58,720
Just think, there will be 400 covers!

308
00:18:58,745 --> 00:19:03,636
The cultural attaché will come on purpose
from Paris. Are you listening to me?

309
00:19:06,440 --> 00:19:11,116
Did you find it?
Did you hurt yourself?

310
00:19:11,280 --> 00:19:14,600
Hurry up, mother's guests
will arrive in 15 minutes.

311
00:19:22,760 --> 00:19:24,420
Here it is!

312
00:19:24,445 --> 00:19:26,195
How does Anne-Lise look to you?

313
00:19:26,220 --> 00:19:27,221
I like.

314
00:19:27,246 --> 00:19:31,194
I am glad because
he gave us the most beautiful gift.

315
00:19:31,360 --> 00:19:33,427
Huh? What gift?

316
00:19:33,451 --> 00:19:35,146
Location.

317
00:19:35,171 --> 00:19:36,172
I already have it.

318
00:19:36,197 --> 00:19:38,286
No. You have a job.

319
00:19:38,310 --> 00:19:39,476
What difference does it make?

320
00:19:39,501 --> 00:19:41,449
A working man's wife

321
00:19:41,473 --> 00:19:44,077
wears a fur coat of
rabbit instead of mink.

322
00:19:44,102 --> 00:19:45,535
Take Mom for example...

323
00:19:45,559 --> 00:19:47,817
his dinner costs the same as
three days of vacation.

324
00:19:47,842 --> 00:19:50,951
Since she has been married, she has been using the furniture
she received from her mother-in-law.

325
00:19:50,976 --> 00:19:52,231
Don't worry!

326
00:19:52,255 --> 00:19:55,353
You'll get the mink when I find
The secret to slowing down life.

327
00:19:55,378 --> 00:19:58,194
No. I also like it from rabbit.

328
00:19:58,360 --> 00:20:02,069
Well, if I don't find the slowdown
Of life, I have my super vitamin.

329
00:20:02,240 --> 00:20:04,633
A rabbit takes
3 kilograms in two days.

330
00:20:05,053 --> 00:20:09,386
Nobody wants to get fat!
People want just the opposite.

331
00:20:09,411 --> 00:20:14,429
Listen,
Anne-Lise is giving us an unhoped-for opportunity.

332
00:20:14,600 --> 00:20:18,908
Give dad your resignation
And in a month's time,

333
00:20:18,933 --> 00:20:22,350
You go into private industry, okay?

334
00:20:33,760 --> 00:20:38,161
The dogs, the carp!
The rabbits, the doves, the mice!

335
00:20:38,185 --> 00:20:39,906
Is this a description of Noah's Ark?

336
00:20:40,040 --> 00:20:42,554
It is not acquiring the results.

337
00:20:42,720 --> 00:20:44,608
Turn everything off.

338
00:20:44,632 --> 00:20:47,408
But how,
six weeks of observations...

339
00:20:47,432 --> 00:20:48,633
Turn everything off.

340
00:20:57,880 --> 00:20:58,920
Do we start from scratch?

341
00:20:58,945 --> 00:21:01,077
No, we're stopping!

342
00:21:01,240 --> 00:21:02,628
So do we release them all?

343
00:21:02,652 --> 00:21:05,588
Momo, Bertrand, Jules,
Zoe, Gustave, Caroline, Alfred...

344
00:21:05,613 --> 00:21:07,721
Are they the calendar saints?

345
00:21:07,745 --> 00:21:12,375
I have given names to all of them...
except for these who were born yesterday.

346
00:21:12,400 --> 00:21:15,392
I'm leaving!
I'm leaving the laboratory!

347
00:21:15,560 --> 00:21:19,114
I will have a new, much better one.
Unlimited credit.

348
00:21:19,139 --> 00:21:22,556
But it is wonderful!
Nothing to be sad about!

349
00:21:22,720 --> 00:21:27,191
Unlimited credit, but no Momo,
no Arthur or Caroline.

350
00:21:27,360 --> 00:21:29,061
All research

351
00:21:29,085 --> 00:21:34,495
Will revolve around the improvement
of humanity through gazoses and tonics.

352
00:21:34,520 --> 00:21:35,528
Like the Juvacola?

353
00:21:35,552 --> 00:21:36,796
Exactly.

354
00:21:36,960 --> 00:21:38,775
"Juvacola-super.

355
00:21:38,800 --> 00:21:42,191
And that's why you leave your job?

356
00:21:42,960 --> 00:21:45,156
With the results obtained...

357
00:21:45,320 --> 00:21:50,566
734 changes to my formula and
only so many disappearing ants!

358
00:21:51,760 --> 00:21:54,915
Professor, can I go?
My train is in 27 minutes.

359
00:21:54,940 --> 00:21:55,940
Where are you going?

360
00:21:55,965 --> 00:22:00,526
Professor, do you remember that I have a leave of absence
of 15 days? I'm going to my grandmother's.

361
00:22:00,551 --> 00:22:01,555
Go.

362
00:22:01,579 --> 00:22:03,238
Thank you, professor.

363
00:22:05,600 --> 00:22:07,948
Is there no chance...?

364
00:22:10,085 --> 00:22:12,935
None.
It would take a miracle.

365
00:22:12,959 --> 00:22:14,071
All right, I'll take it all out.

366
00:22:23,080 --> 00:22:24,639
Don't worry, Atom.

367
00:22:37,280 --> 00:22:40,520
Did he want a miracle?

368
00:22:40,544 --> 00:22:42,153
It worked.

369
00:22:43,960 --> 00:22:45,955
Yes! It worked! It worked!

370
00:22:45,979 --> 00:22:47,835
The ants were
too small to see.

371
00:22:47,860 --> 00:22:49,980
She never wears her
glasses when she needs them.

372
00:22:50,004 --> 00:22:51,313
Calm down, we understand the method.

373
00:22:51,338 --> 00:22:54,756
Maybe there is no method.
She is always observing

374
00:22:54,920 --> 00:22:57,335
It is necessary to observe,
to gain experience.

375
00:22:57,359 --> 00:22:58,879
I don't talk about the experiences.

376
00:22:58,904 --> 00:23:01,421
It is not always important
that the calculations are right.

377
00:23:01,446 --> 00:23:03,113
Chance also plays a role.

378
00:23:03,180 --> 00:23:07,035
What if Newton had not
dropped the apple on his nose?

379
00:23:08,120 --> 00:23:10,430
His apple is my little Atom.

380
00:23:12,000 --> 00:23:13,615
My little Atom...

381
00:23:13,639 --> 00:23:17,839
No, no, no ... you are my apple ...

382
00:23:19,480 --> 00:23:22,791
Hmm... Good. Let's go in order!

383
00:23:22,960 --> 00:23:25,110
Or maybe it's better to
make some messes.

384
00:23:26,080 --> 00:23:29,913
Another ant and
another vial of N734.

385
00:23:51,160 --> 00:23:52,195
Here.

386
00:23:57,280 --> 00:24:00,040
Ants, ants,
ants, the whole anthill!

387
00:24:07,493 --> 00:24:10,110
Ah,
my experience is worthless.

388
00:24:11,826 --> 00:24:14,754
Female intuition...

389
00:24:27,540 --> 00:24:29,195
Always late!

390
00:24:29,219 --> 00:24:30,681
We don't go to your father.

391
00:24:30,706 --> 00:24:31,821
Why?

392
00:24:33,605 --> 00:24:36,946
Ah! Why did you decide
to sell knick-knacks?

393
00:24:36,971 --> 00:24:38,481
Much better!

394
00:24:38,506 --> 00:24:39,506
Meaning?

395
00:24:39,531 --> 00:24:43,381
But how?
My N734 solution works.

396
00:24:43,406 --> 00:24:47,677
This was a real rabbit. And this one
Was a real guinea pig.

397
00:24:48,320 --> 00:24:51,961
The indefinite conservation
Of matter. Here it is.

398
00:24:51,985 --> 00:24:53,679
The ants have not disappeared.

399
00:24:53,840 --> 00:24:56,719
They turned to stone,
decreasing in size!

400
00:24:56,880 --> 00:24:58,868
Are you saying that
these are real animals?

401
00:24:58,892 --> 00:24:59,921
But yes!

402
00:24:59,945 --> 00:25:01,080
But it's disgusting!

403
00:25:02,600 --> 00:25:07,513
This cannot
be serious!

404
00:25:07,680 --> 00:25:11,071
Because of these ridiculous little things,
you wanted to change our plans?

405
00:25:11,240 --> 00:25:12,594
For what purpose then?

406
00:25:12,760 --> 00:25:16,228
You have invented a new way
To kill poor animals.

407
00:25:16,253 --> 00:25:17,952
This is nothing to brag about.

408
00:25:18,520 --> 00:25:22,068
And of course, you don't know how to revive them?
Don't you?

409
00:25:22,093 --> 00:25:23,093
But.

410
00:25:23,118 --> 00:25:25,838
Okay, let's go.
Father is waiting for us.

411
00:25:26,000 --> 00:25:29,654
I told him you had resigned.
He felt sorry for you,

412
00:25:29,679 --> 00:25:32,846
But of course, the happiness of
his daughter comes first.

413
00:25:42,686 --> 00:25:46,959
Aren't you thirsty? Go ahead, drink up.

414
00:25:50,299 --> 00:25:53,870
That's it!
Did you see how easy it was?

415
00:25:53,895 --> 00:25:55,839
One always thinks one is
to be indispensable

416
00:25:55,863 --> 00:25:57,807
And instead they are happy
when one leaves.

417
00:25:57,832 --> 00:26:00,957
Especially that colleague of yours
who can take over your laboratory.

418
00:26:00,982 --> 00:26:04,105
Perhaps your method can
be used in the industry of

419
00:26:04,129 --> 00:26:07,717
chimney linings.
Obviously it will be very expensive, but ...

420
00:26:07,880 --> 00:26:11,820
Perhaps I can revive them.
The research takes time.

421
00:26:11,845 --> 00:26:16,149
How long did it take before
your beasts became petrified?

422
00:26:16,320 --> 00:26:17,640
3 years.

423
00:26:19,200 --> 00:26:22,875
You have 15 days to
try to revive them.

424
00:26:25,880 --> 00:26:30,317
Next, preparations for the
wedding. Then, 15 days in Paris.

425
00:26:30,480 --> 00:26:34,921
You are going to Juvacola on August 1.
In the meantime, you can have fun here.

426
00:26:34,946 --> 00:26:36,401
Chief, look!

427
00:26:36,425 --> 00:26:37,792
Yeah ... you have fun ...

428
00:26:37,960 --> 00:26:41,635
I don't think I know her.
Who is this lovely young lady?

429
00:26:41,800 --> 00:26:43,068
Monette...

430
00:26:43,092 --> 00:26:45,871
Monette Landry,
assistant professor Norman.

431
00:26:45,980 --> 00:26:46,981
Sorry for the interruption.

432
00:26:47,005 --> 00:26:49,177
No, no, not at all!
No interruption.

433
00:26:49,202 --> 00:26:51,966
I came for Monette. If the
Mr. Norman is finished with her...

434
00:26:51,990 --> 00:26:53,063
No, we are not finished!

435
00:26:53,200 --> 00:26:56,935
I thought you didn't know her.
She is pretty...

436
00:26:56,960 --> 00:27:01,079
Yes, yes, yes, yes.
Very nice. Even too much so.

437
00:27:01,240 --> 00:27:04,215
Your colleagues are envious
And they will start gossiping.

438
00:27:04,240 --> 00:27:06,436
Father will suffer so much....

439
00:27:06,461 --> 00:27:10,753
I am not jealous, I want the
best for your career... Hey!

440
00:27:11,220 --> 00:27:13,909
Mr. Prade,
the young lady needs to be with

441
00:27:13,933 --> 00:27:16,621
my fiancé,
would you mind accompanying me?

442
00:27:16,646 --> 00:27:17,869
With pleasure.

443
00:27:18,040 --> 00:27:20,554
Let's leave the scientists
to their own work.

444
00:27:22,640 --> 00:27:23,968
Can I take the dog with me?

445
00:27:23,993 --> 00:27:24,993
No.

446
00:27:25,906 --> 00:27:26,906
The dog.

447
00:27:30,760 --> 00:27:31,769
It is moving.

448
00:27:31,794 --> 00:27:32,794
Do you think so?

449
00:27:32,819 --> 00:27:34,719
It seems to me. Shall we open?

450
00:27:35,400 --> 00:27:36,993
No. Two more minutes.

451
00:27:42,800 --> 00:27:43,868
What are you doing?

452
00:27:43,892 --> 00:27:48,038
I promise St. Lazarus to
Return the collar I stole.

453
00:27:48,840 --> 00:27:50,155
Why St. Lazarus?

454
00:27:50,179 --> 00:27:51,966
He is the patron saint of the resurrected.

455
00:27:54,240 --> 00:27:59,030
Nothing.
Maybe you stole two collars.

456
00:28:43,440 --> 00:28:45,113
Damn!

457
00:28:47,453 --> 00:28:49,155
This was my last hope.

458
00:28:49,179 --> 00:28:50,997
And our last day.

459
00:28:51,160 --> 00:28:54,135
Don't cry. I will find you
A much better leader than I am.

460
00:28:54,160 --> 00:28:56,276
There is no one better than you.

461
00:29:09,560 --> 00:29:12,622
I have been waiting for it for 15 days....

462
00:29:12,646 --> 00:29:13,742
15 days?

463
00:29:13,766 --> 00:29:14,796
Yes.

464
00:29:14,960 --> 00:29:18,178
Ever since I realized that
you don't love your girlfriend.

465
00:29:19,412 --> 00:29:21,300
You keep crying though...

466
00:29:21,324 --> 00:29:22,498
Of joy.

467
00:29:29,726 --> 00:29:31,955
But what...?

468
00:29:31,979 --> 00:29:33,110
What?

469
00:29:34,040 --> 00:29:35,440
Quick, quick, come here.

470
00:29:36,393 --> 00:29:38,588
No no!
We need to figure out what's going on!

471
00:29:38,612 --> 00:29:40,235
I am afraid!

472
00:29:40,346 --> 00:29:43,791
The tears! The tears! Water
Salted in the proportion of 0.033!

473
00:29:44,000 --> 00:29:45,991
Come on, cry now!

474
00:29:47,034 --> 00:29:48,034
Cry!

475
00:29:48,059 --> 00:29:49,197
I can't!

476
00:29:49,360 --> 00:29:51,556
Yes, of course. Always the same story!

477
00:29:51,720 --> 00:29:54,274
When it is not necessary,
you cry, and when it is needed.

478
00:29:54,299 --> 00:29:55,698
You are a monster!

479
00:29:55,760 --> 00:29:58,326
For you, tears are
only 0.033 saline solution!

480
00:29:58,600 --> 00:30:02,895
My tears are pain!
I am in pain!

481
00:30:03,566 --> 00:30:07,793
Brava! Brava.
Brava. Cry! Cry! Cry!

482
00:30:09,106 --> 00:30:10,326
Come on.

483
00:30:11,960 --> 00:30:13,075
Come on!

484
00:30:14,746 --> 00:30:15,746
Again!

485
00:30:32,720 --> 00:30:34,358
It does not work.

486
00:30:34,520 --> 00:30:37,239
Maybe it only works with ants?

487
00:30:37,960 --> 00:30:39,359
I don't think so.

488
00:30:40,280 --> 00:30:43,671
Probably, you have to immerse it
completely in the solution.

489
00:30:44,320 --> 00:30:47,312
Do you want me to cry so much?

490
00:30:55,960 --> 00:30:58,190
Here it is. It's 198 grams.

491
00:31:09,520 --> 00:31:11,601
Damn!

492
00:31:11,625 --> 00:31:13,909
It is not enough that it is covered.

493
00:31:15,040 --> 00:31:16,792
The volume of salt water

494
00:31:16,960 --> 00:31:21,238
Must be greater than the size
of the living animal's body.

495
00:31:39,800 --> 00:31:41,290
Oh no! No, no!

496
00:31:55,143 --> 00:31:56,975
Phone.

497
00:31:57,000 --> 00:31:58,428
Let it ring.

498
00:31:58,452 --> 00:31:59,468
Answer.

499
00:31:59,493 --> 00:32:00,768
No. Let me...

500
00:32:00,792 --> 00:32:02,199
Go!

501
00:32:11,480 --> 00:32:12,550
Hello?

502
00:32:13,720 --> 00:32:15,518
What? Ah, is that you?

503
00:32:16,800 --> 00:32:19,076
No, no, honey.

504
00:32:19,101 --> 00:32:20,694
What do you mean, "honey?"

505
00:32:21,000 --> 00:32:23,753
No, no, I worked.

506
00:32:27,080 --> 00:32:31,278
If I experiment, it is
because I trust in success.

507
00:32:32,840 --> 00:32:37,313
No, I would rather not kill
beasts and have dinner with you.

508
00:32:38,120 --> 00:32:42,835
Eh, it's quite dangerous.
It could all blow up.

509
00:32:42,860 --> 00:32:44,335
Do you know what you should do?

510
00:32:44,360 --> 00:32:47,615
Eat some chocolates and
go to bed without waiting for me

511
00:32:47,640 --> 00:32:51,429
And later, when I get home,
I will say good night to you

512
00:32:51,600 --> 00:32:56,319
What do you mean if I'm alone here?
Of course, I am alone.

513
00:32:56,480 --> 00:33:00,078
At this time then.
All right, see you soon.

514
00:33:00,240 --> 00:33:01,808
What is it?

515
00:33:01,832 --> 00:33:03,275
My fiancée.

516
00:33:03,299 --> 00:33:04,559
No, it is not.

517
00:33:04,720 --> 00:33:08,395
She is my fiancée, my
fiancée reduced to an equation.

518
00:33:08,560 --> 00:33:11,757
It's simple.
Do you know the arithmetic of passion?

519
00:33:11,782 --> 00:33:14,833
What about that philosopher? Jeremy Bentham?

520
00:33:15,000 --> 00:33:17,389
What were you doing in the classroom?

521
00:33:18,640 --> 00:33:20,048
I used to draw the professor.

522
00:33:20,072 --> 00:33:22,110
Ah, good. Great!

523
00:33:22,280 --> 00:33:24,188
So, the philosopher Jeremy...

524
00:33:24,212 --> 00:33:27,437
Bentham.
He invented the arithmetic of the passions.

525
00:33:27,538 --> 00:33:30,126
For example, if you are offered
a trip to Italy

526
00:33:30,151 --> 00:33:33,634
And you don't know what to do,
make two columns.

527
00:33:34,280 --> 00:33:35,714
In the one on the right,

528
00:33:35,880 --> 00:33:39,635
take notes on what you
like and left the opposite.

529
00:33:39,800 --> 00:33:43,031
Therefore, the grades will be
proportionate to your pleasure.

530
00:33:43,200 --> 00:33:45,135
For example, right...

531
00:33:45,159 --> 00:33:46,272
The things I like.

532
00:33:46,953 --> 00:33:51,390
Yes. So.
"Change of scenery - 8.

533
00:33:52,120 --> 00:33:57,674
"Enrichment of
experience and culture" - 8.5.

534
00:33:57,699 --> 00:34:00,552
"Traveling in sleeping car together" - 10.

535
00:34:01,560 --> 00:34:02,595
10...

536
00:34:02,760 --> 00:34:04,780
"Buying new clothes" - 9.

537
00:34:04,805 --> 00:34:05,855
9...

538
00:34:05,880 --> 00:34:08,780
"Seeing Capri" - 7.
"Buying new hats..."

539
00:34:08,805 --> 00:34:11,600
- 7... Wait a minute!
- 8.5. - 8.5...

540
00:34:12,720 --> 00:34:14,548
"Visiting museums" - 8.

541
00:34:14,572 --> 00:34:16,033
Oh. 2.

542
00:34:17,040 --> 00:34:19,077
2. Well, that's enough.

543
00:34:19,240 --> 00:34:22,073
Now in the second column
mark what you don't like.

544
00:34:22,240 --> 00:34:25,039
Nothing. With you I like everything.

545
00:34:25,200 --> 00:34:27,486
- Do you want to learn or not?
- Yes.

546
00:34:27,511 --> 00:34:30,157
Do the additions and
decide whether to make the trip

547
00:34:30,182 --> 00:34:32,526
based on the column
that has the highest total.

548
00:34:32,550 --> 00:34:34,216
Same thing with my girlfriend.

549
00:34:34,241 --> 00:34:38,034
I write on the right what makes her
angry, on the left what calms her down.

550
00:34:38,200 --> 00:34:40,191
Two additions, one subtraction.

551
00:34:40,360 --> 00:34:44,815
And depending on the outcome,
I am calm, firm or lovely.

552
00:34:44,840 --> 00:34:47,021
And are you often forced
to be lovely?

553
00:34:47,045 --> 00:34:50,893
Oh, it's not that terrible at all,
thanks to my kindness...

554
00:34:50,917 --> 00:34:51,920
Your kindness is exaggerated.

555
00:34:51,945 --> 00:34:55,718
Edith is waiting for me to
drop by to say good night to her.

556
00:34:57,406 --> 00:34:59,256
- Shut up, Atom!
- Who's there?

557
00:34:59,280 --> 00:35:01,808
Open up! Why have you locked yourself in?

558
00:35:01,833 --> 00:35:03,428
Who is it? Is it you?

559
00:35:03,453 --> 00:35:04,455
It is not so terrible...

560
00:35:04,480 --> 00:35:05,636
It's me, Edith!

561
00:35:08,226 --> 00:35:10,068
I know you are not alone! Open!

562
00:35:10,093 --> 00:35:13,655
I'm sure that
girl is with you! Open up now!

563
00:35:13,680 --> 00:35:15,315
I can't now!

564
00:35:15,339 --> 00:35:17,470
Open up, quickly!

565
00:35:17,640 --> 00:35:19,571
I am just finishing an experiment!

566
00:35:19,596 --> 00:35:22,850
An experiment! I can imagine what
kind of experiment you are doing!

567
00:35:23,160 --> 00:35:26,346
Can you hear me? Open or I'll break down the door!

568
00:35:26,371 --> 00:35:28,508
Here, here, here, here I come!

569
00:35:28,532 --> 00:35:30,695
I warn you, I'm going to scream!

570
00:35:30,720 --> 00:35:32,865
You are wasting time.

571
00:35:35,240 --> 00:35:39,393
I will scream so loud that
the whole neighborhood will hear!

572
00:35:39,560 --> 00:35:42,200
Jerome! Open!

573
00:35:42,800 --> 00:35:44,873
I'm going to scream!

574
00:35:46,840 --> 00:35:49,559
If you don't open on 3, I'll scream!

575
00:35:49,760 --> 00:35:51,512
I'm starting to count! One!

576
00:35:52,800 --> 00:35:54,635
Two!

577
00:35:54,659 --> 00:35:55,949
I'm coming!

578
00:35:56,120 --> 00:35:59,200
Jerome, open now!

579
00:36:09,533 --> 00:36:10,895
What are you doing?

580
00:36:10,919 --> 00:36:11,981
Where is she?

581
00:36:12,006 --> 00:36:13,855
- She who?
- He said, "Shut up, Atom."

582
00:36:13,880 --> 00:36:14,880
Shut up, Atom!

583
00:36:15,880 --> 00:36:17,041
Shut up, Atom!

584
00:36:17,065 --> 00:36:18,672
You see for yourself...

585
00:36:25,753 --> 00:36:27,615
I must conclude,
my dear Edith,

586
00:36:27,640 --> 00:36:30,233
that you are not the
ideal for a researcher.

587
00:36:30,258 --> 00:36:33,452
I, I am the one who will make you
win the Pavlov Prize!

588
00:36:33,477 --> 00:36:36,039
You confuse rewards and results.

589
00:36:36,200 --> 00:36:39,892
Awards mean nothing. What
that matters are their motivations.

590
00:36:39,917 --> 00:36:41,518
I will take care of the Pavlov Prize.

591
00:36:41,727 --> 00:36:44,046
No, no, from now on
I will take care of everything.

592
00:36:44,071 --> 00:36:46,400
First of all,
tomorrow I will withdraw my resignation

593
00:36:46,425 --> 00:36:48,135
And I will not leave my workshop.

594
00:36:48,160 --> 00:36:52,631
And I will tell Madame Juvacola
That she can croak. That's it!

595
00:36:53,500 --> 00:36:55,755
Do you realize that you are
you are ruining my life?

596
00:36:55,780 --> 00:36:59,091
If I ruin your life, you are free
to take back your word.

597
00:37:01,753 --> 00:37:04,063
And now, good night.
I need to work.

598
00:37:05,640 --> 00:37:07,995
And alone!

599
00:37:20,240 --> 00:37:23,603
So.
Aren't we done yet?

600
00:37:23,627 --> 00:37:24,749
No.

601
00:37:26,320 --> 00:37:28,516
And you don't say good night?

602
00:37:31,320 --> 00:37:32,435
Good night.

603
00:37:33,886 --> 00:37:35,559
I did not hear.

604
00:37:39,506 --> 00:37:40,780
Good night.

605
00:37:43,640 --> 00:37:44,710
Good.

606
00:38:54,560 --> 00:38:56,241
Here! No, to the right!

607
00:38:56,266 --> 00:38:57,381
Bataillon!

608
00:38:57,405 --> 00:39:00,013
Pay attention and follow along!

609
00:39:00,306 --> 00:39:01,973
Aren't you up yet?

610
00:39:02,312 --> 00:39:05,015
No, no, the box there and
the plant on the porch.

611
00:39:05,040 --> 00:39:06,241
But what's going on?

612
00:39:06,265 --> 00:39:08,761
How what happens.
Items are delivered.

613
00:39:08,786 --> 00:39:12,281
When the utensils arrive
from the kitchen, Solange will clean everything.

614
00:39:12,306 --> 00:39:13,881
Aren't you going to the workshop?

615
00:39:13,905 --> 00:39:15,054
There is not much to do.

616
00:39:15,079 --> 00:39:16,814
- Your breakfast, sir.
- Thank you.

617
00:39:16,839 --> 00:39:19,599
Mom and dad are waiting for me.
If you want, meet me at 1:30?

618
00:39:19,624 --> 00:39:22,311
I have to run.
I have a thousand things to do. Bye!

619
00:39:22,480 --> 00:39:23,629
Hello.

620
00:39:40,720 --> 00:39:42,355
Solange!

621
00:39:42,380 --> 00:39:43,380
Sir?

622
00:39:43,405 --> 00:39:45,910
Salt! So much salt!

623
00:39:46,080 --> 00:39:47,375
Table salt?

624
00:39:47,399 --> 00:39:50,961
Yes, table salt
And a kitchen scale.

625
00:39:50,985 --> 00:39:52,351
All right, sir.

626
00:39:59,720 --> 00:40:03,350
Someone will now take
will take a bath.

627
00:40:10,720 --> 00:40:12,745
Here, sir.

628
00:40:12,769 --> 00:40:14,080
Well thank you.

629
00:40:17,960 --> 00:40:19,312
Is that all we have?

630
00:40:19,337 --> 00:40:20,728
There is enough for a week.

631
00:40:20,753 --> 00:40:24,190
You need to have a supply
of salt for at least a month!

632
00:40:24,360 --> 00:40:27,830
What if we run out of it?
Come on, go get me some salt.

633
00:40:28,000 --> 00:40:30,115
Find me the salt! Please!

634
00:40:30,139 --> 00:40:31,205
Yes, sir.

635
00:40:31,230 --> 00:40:32,483
Solange, what's going on?

636
00:40:32,508 --> 00:40:37,514
Madam, the gentleman scolded me
about the salt. I run to bring it to him.

637
00:40:38,440 --> 00:40:39,440
Enter.

638
00:40:40,073 --> 00:40:41,075
Here, sir.

639
00:40:41,099 --> 00:40:43,732
Ah, thank you. Thank you, you can go.

640
00:40:54,629 --> 00:40:56,818
Solange! There is no water!

641
00:40:56,842 --> 00:40:59,362
The plumbing system is
under repair, monsieur.

642
00:41:00,120 --> 00:41:02,555
Ouch, what a house!

643
00:41:09,120 --> 00:41:11,895
Maubru.
I need a large vessel.

644
00:41:11,920 --> 00:41:13,655
Professor,
do you think I got a tan?

645
00:41:13,679 --> 00:41:15,959
I want a big vessel!

646
00:41:16,120 --> 00:41:18,121
This big?

647
00:41:18,145 --> 00:41:19,951
As large as possible.

648
00:41:20,120 --> 00:41:22,919
The biggest one has it
Mr. Bataillon.

649
00:41:33,360 --> 00:41:34,456
Maubru.

650
00:41:37,200 --> 00:41:38,599
Wish?

651
00:41:38,760 --> 00:41:42,168
I... I was admiring the
his bath in the cistern.

652
00:41:42,193 --> 00:41:43,728
It is neither a toilet nor a cistern!

653
00:41:43,753 --> 00:41:46,335
This is the "Aquadinamometer
Bataillon model."

654
00:41:46,360 --> 00:41:47,734
Would you like to lend it to me?

655
00:41:47,758 --> 00:41:51,631
The experiment he interrupted
will last until 2 a.m.

656
00:41:51,656 --> 00:41:55,793
Also, I don't lend my
Bataillon aquadynamometer to anyone

657
00:41:55,818 --> 00:41:57,158
Until I have it patented.

658
00:41:57,440 --> 00:42:01,389
And even after the patent,
I will not lend it to you!

659
00:42:08,600 --> 00:42:10,716
Throw everything in the trash.

660
00:42:13,320 --> 00:42:15,789
Too bad. They were beautiful.

661
00:42:16,000 --> 00:42:21,306
25 cubic decimeters with 0.033 solution...

662
00:42:22,000 --> 00:42:29,479
If the tank is larger, I will add
7.85 grams -- plus 10 cubes....

663
00:42:29,807 --> 00:42:31,546
LE BISON BATHROOMS

664
00:42:42,391 --> 00:42:45,853
It is strictly forbidden to introduce
into the tank products brought from home.

665
00:42:45,878 --> 00:42:48,498
If you want bath salts,
he can purchase it at the checkout.

666
00:42:54,120 --> 00:42:55,508
That's fine, I'll take it.

667
00:42:55,532 --> 00:42:59,191
Made to order only.
Delivery in three weeks.

668
00:43:42,440 --> 00:43:43,999
Hey! Taxi!

669
00:44:51,800 --> 00:44:53,871
No jokes, huh?

670
00:45:29,040 --> 00:45:32,431
Jerome,
swear that you will love me forever.

671
00:45:34,120 --> 00:45:35,315
How should I know?

672
00:45:35,480 --> 00:45:38,518
In that case,
how do you think I could trust it?

673
00:45:38,680 --> 00:45:40,881
Trust who? Me?

674
00:45:40,905 --> 00:45:42,310
No, about me.

675
00:45:43,520 --> 00:45:47,559
If I'm not sure forever,
then what's the point of loving you today?

676
00:45:49,600 --> 00:45:51,796
Perhaps to be happy.

677
00:45:51,960 --> 00:45:55,510
Do you think it's easy to be happy?
It is very, very difficult.

678
00:45:55,680 --> 00:45:59,281
Also particularly long.
I've been waiting for you for 30 hours.

679
00:45:59,305 --> 00:46:00,305
But...!

680
00:46:00,800 --> 00:46:03,918
30 hours! Maybe you are starving?

681
00:46:04,080 --> 00:46:05,501
Why should I?

682
00:46:05,525 --> 00:46:09,555
But 30 hours. 30 hours you haven't eaten.
Aren't you hungry?

683
00:46:09,579 --> 00:46:10,579
No.

684
00:46:10,604 --> 00:46:13,053
Yes, yes, yes, yes...

685
00:46:13,078 --> 00:46:14,580
What is it? Do I look bad?

686
00:46:14,604 --> 00:46:15,615
No, no.

687
00:46:15,640 --> 00:46:17,826
Breathe. Breathe.

688
00:46:18,200 --> 00:46:19,740
Breathe! Breathe deep!

689
00:46:19,765 --> 00:46:21,152
You crush me.

690
00:46:25,000 --> 00:46:26,568
Your hand.

691
00:46:26,592 --> 00:46:27,761
Don't you like it?

692
00:46:27,785 --> 00:46:28,994
I like it, I like it.

693
00:46:29,600 --> 00:46:30,954
How do I look?

694
00:46:31,560 --> 00:46:32,908
I don't know.

695
00:46:32,932 --> 00:46:34,395
How does he look?

696
00:46:34,419 --> 00:46:35,549
I don't know.

697
00:46:37,460 --> 00:46:38,460
Good.

698
00:46:38,485 --> 00:46:41,028
Are you going to x-ray me
next time?

699
00:46:42,400 --> 00:46:46,792
Next time I will get you
the pressure before and after.

700
00:46:47,720 --> 00:46:52,433
And tomorrow I will start drafting my
my communication to the Academy.

701
00:47:16,240 --> 00:47:17,759
Back from class?

702
00:47:17,784 --> 00:47:20,794
Yes,
"study of aquatic mammals."

703
00:47:20,819 --> 00:47:22,068
Is this a joke?

704
00:47:22,093 --> 00:47:23,194
No, I wouldn't dare.

705
00:47:23,218 --> 00:47:27,120
I have responsibilities!
Therefore, I need to know...

706
00:47:27,144 --> 00:47:28,198
...everything, miss?

707
00:47:28,280 --> 00:47:31,793
18.30 - I leave the faculty,
8 p.m. - I have dinner with a childhood friend,

708
00:47:31,818 --> 00:47:33,675
10 p.m. - Let's go to the movies.
Midnight, at her place.

709
00:47:33,700 --> 00:47:36,581
At her house? Is she a girl?

710
00:47:36,606 --> 00:47:39,221
And finally, today at noon
we were at the beach.

711
00:47:39,246 --> 00:47:40,674
Monette. Where have you been?

712
00:47:40,699 --> 00:47:42,414
Mr. Prade,
forget the white step!

713
00:47:42,439 --> 00:47:43,500
I have to change.

714
00:47:43,524 --> 00:47:44,895
Wait...!

715
00:47:44,920 --> 00:47:46,479
Mr. Prade, the white step!

716
00:47:46,503 --> 00:47:47,705
Excuse me, miss.

717
00:47:47,730 --> 00:47:49,358
- Where are you coming from?
- Can't you see it?

718
00:47:49,383 --> 00:47:50,731
- And before that?
- I had breakfast.

719
00:47:50,755 --> 00:47:53,784
- Where? Were you alone?
- At the Grand Dukes'. I was not alone.

720
00:47:53,809 --> 00:47:58,203
Ah, you were with him. The Don Juan
of the Amphitheater, the future Nobel laureate.

721
00:47:58,228 --> 00:48:00,136
How about you? How is the beautiful Edith?

722
00:48:00,161 --> 00:48:02,062
Who were you with at the end?

723
00:48:02,086 --> 00:48:03,176
- With my uncle.
- What?

724
00:48:03,200 --> 00:48:05,895
Yes, with my uncle.
Now leave me alone.

725
00:48:05,920 --> 00:48:08,255
If you think I'm running after you ...

726
00:48:08,280 --> 00:48:10,733
I don't think it, I see it.

727
00:48:18,080 --> 00:48:19,555
To the two of us, I heard it all!

728
00:48:19,580 --> 00:48:21,008
Perfect, are you spying on me now?

729
00:48:21,032 --> 00:48:22,393
Not out here, come in.

730
00:48:22,418 --> 00:48:25,831
You have no childhood friends or an uncle.
Confession.

731
00:48:26,000 --> 00:48:27,399
I don't want to tell lies.

732
00:48:27,423 --> 00:48:28,815
Then tell the truth.

733
00:48:28,840 --> 00:48:31,478
No one has ever made my
my heart beat faster.

734
00:48:31,503 --> 00:48:32,588
Is it that exciting?

735
00:48:32,612 --> 00:48:33,839
Rockin'!

736
00:48:35,760 --> 00:48:37,593
Good. I'm listening.

737
00:48:37,617 --> 00:48:38,981
You're not going to tell anyone?

738
00:48:39,006 --> 00:48:40,455
I never say anything.

739
00:48:40,479 --> 00:48:43,820
Look, the day before yesterday, Juliette
told me, in secret,

740
00:48:43,844 --> 00:48:46,400
that she was in love
with her Uncle Gilbert.

741
00:48:46,560 --> 00:48:49,712
Did I tell you? No.
Then what?

742
00:48:49,920 --> 00:48:52,389
Well, I love a man.

743
00:48:53,560 --> 00:48:55,471
And he loves me.

744
00:48:55,680 --> 00:48:59,275
We spent the night together.
We had breakfast in the countryside.

745
00:48:59,440 --> 00:49:01,351
We took a bath.
We were soaked.

746
00:49:01,376 --> 00:49:04,055
- I don't believe you, it's not possible.
- But it's true!

747
00:49:04,080 --> 00:49:06,020
But if it is true, what is exciting about it?

748
00:49:06,440 --> 00:49:11,981
Oh, Professor.
This dog barks day and night.

749
00:49:12,005 --> 00:49:14,511
Mr. Bataillon threatens
to press charges.

750
00:49:15,440 --> 00:49:18,693
Go and buy me
cigarettes before they close.

751
00:49:18,717 --> 00:49:19,717
Good.

752
00:49:29,545 --> 00:49:30,738
So.

753
00:49:57,280 --> 00:49:59,335
Chief, where is the dog?

754
00:49:59,359 --> 00:50:00,989
What dog?

755
00:50:04,800 --> 00:50:08,077
So where did you spend the night?
With whom? It's not Jean-Loup.

756
00:50:08,240 --> 00:50:11,790
A new one?
Did you ever tell me about him?

757
00:50:11,960 --> 00:50:15,113
There may be reasons
why I never talked about it.

758
00:50:15,253 --> 00:50:16,728
Is the police looking for him?

759
00:50:16,753 --> 00:50:19,592
My story takes place
internationally.

760
00:50:20,720 --> 00:50:22,472
