- Not me, my best friend.

1003
01:12:02,460 --> 01:12:03,995
Is he reporting it?

1004
01:12:04,019 --> 01:12:05,121
He is in mortal danger!

1005
01:12:05,939 --> 01:12:08,081
Professor Norman is
involved in this story.

1006
01:12:08,105 --> 01:12:09,354
Norman.

1007
01:12:09,379 --> 01:12:12,335
Commissioner, you should see the
guy I've been questioning for an hour.

1008
01:12:12,360 --> 01:12:14,340
- Who is he.
- A biology professor, Norman.

1009
01:12:14,365 --> 01:12:16,556
On the disappearance
Miss Landry.

1010
01:12:16,720 --> 01:12:18,961
It is a case without interest.
It is a simple escape.

1011
01:12:18,986 --> 01:12:20,788
I thought so, too.

1012
01:12:20,812 --> 01:12:23,355
But he looks so strange that
I wonder if he's not involved.

1013
01:12:23,380 --> 01:12:24,495
Okay.

1014
01:12:33,160 --> 01:12:36,415
Maybe. I wouldn't be surprised if
He had strangled the girl.

1015
01:12:36,440 --> 01:12:38,829
After the classic rape.

1016
01:12:42,320 --> 01:12:44,215
- Commissioner Andre.
- Jerome Norman.

1017
01:12:44,240 --> 01:12:47,581
She knows my son. He is following
his course... Francois Andre.

1018
01:12:47,606 --> 01:12:49,868
Curly blondie.
His father's portrait.

1019
01:12:49,893 --> 01:12:51,108
Ah, yes, yes, yes...

1020
01:12:51,133 --> 01:12:52,466
I heard about yesterday's misunderstanding,

1021
01:12:52,491 --> 01:12:54,516
a mistake for which I wanted to
apologize in person.

1022
01:12:54,541 --> 01:12:56,054
Don't worry.

1023
01:12:56,078 --> 01:12:58,196
After all, we are almost colleagues.

1024
01:12:58,221 --> 01:12:59,766
We both do research.

1025
01:13:00,360 --> 01:13:02,808
This case...
is of no interest.

1026
01:13:02,833 --> 01:13:05,568
The girl must be living the perfect
romance with a rogue

1027
01:13:05,593 --> 01:13:10,826
Or she will be found in a few
days in a ditch, torn to pieces.

1028
01:13:11,800 --> 01:13:13,313
The police find out everything.

1029
01:13:15,120 --> 01:13:16,349
Do you feel ill?

1030
01:13:17,493 --> 01:13:18,728
So, professor...?

1031
01:13:18,752 --> 01:13:20,761
No, no, excuse me,
it's hot in here.

1032
01:13:20,786 --> 01:13:22,348
But he is trembling.

1033
01:13:22,372 --> 01:13:23,753
But no, no, not at all.

1034
01:13:23,920 --> 01:13:27,055
I'll take care of it.
Julien, go get some cognac.

1035
01:13:27,080 --> 01:13:30,326
No, no, no, you are very kind.
But I am better now, thank you!

1036
01:13:32,440 --> 01:13:37,801
Commissioner, you told me that the
police always find out everything, right?

1037
01:13:37,826 --> 01:13:39,895
Everything. Are you looking for something?

1038
01:13:39,919 --> 01:13:45,079
Yes, Monette. She is my assistant,
Ms. Landry.

1039
01:13:46,406 --> 01:13:49,695
Commissioner, I ask you to find it!

1040
01:13:49,720 --> 01:13:52,466
Was she a collaborator
so valuable?

1041
01:13:52,560 --> 01:13:57,115
Please, Commissioner,
don't talk about her in the past tense.

1042
01:13:57,140 --> 01:13:59,273
I -- I love her so much.

1043
01:13:59,298 --> 01:14:00,973
I thought I had
read the other day

1044
01:14:00,998 --> 01:14:03,815
the announcement of his marriage
to another person.

1045
01:14:03,840 --> 01:14:07,221
Yes but it is Miss.
Monette Landry that I'm going to marry.

1046
01:14:07,245 --> 01:14:09,513
I asked my fiancée
to dissolve the promise.

1047
01:14:09,538 --> 01:14:10,800
Did she refuse?

1048
01:14:10,824 --> 01:14:13,775
Yes. In order not to quarrel
With his family,

1049
01:14:13,799 --> 01:14:16,479
I stopped living with
them and decided to wait

1050
01:14:16,640 --> 01:14:19,598
the first opportunity that would
advantage with my fiancée.

1051
01:14:19,760 --> 01:14:21,835
He has a very violent character.

1052
01:14:21,860 --> 01:14:24,281
At this time he had
clandestine meetings...

1053
01:14:24,305 --> 01:14:26,648
- ...with Ms. Landry?
- Yes.

1054
01:14:26,673 --> 01:14:28,032
In short, he is insinuating

1055
01:14:28,057 --> 01:14:31,055
That his fiancée might have
have made her rival disappear?

1056
01:14:31,080 --> 01:14:32,715
Not at all!

1057
01:14:32,739 --> 01:14:34,508
Then it is you who killed her!

1058
01:14:34,533 --> 01:14:37,612
Let's face it.
She had a lover who was pushing her to marry her.

1059
01:14:37,637 --> 01:14:39,414
His fiancée
threatened a scandal,

1060
01:14:39,439 --> 01:14:41,234
he felt obliged
by his parents,

1061
01:14:41,258 --> 01:14:42,583
Therefore, he killed the girl.

1062
01:14:42,640 --> 01:14:44,335
But-but-but it's not true!

1063
01:14:44,359 --> 01:14:45,895
Then explain this disappearance!

1064
01:14:45,920 --> 01:14:48,375
I -- I can't.

1065
01:14:48,400 --> 01:14:51,320
When did you last see
Miss Landry the last time?

1066
01:14:51,345 --> 01:14:54,906
4 a.m. Monday at the university.

1067
01:14:54,931 --> 01:14:55,931
What did he do next?

1068
01:14:55,956 --> 01:14:59,101
I had a business interview
with a friend of my girlfriend's.

1069
01:14:59,126 --> 01:15:01,179
What time was it?

1070
01:15:01,204 --> 01:15:03,781
Eh... 5 p.m.

1071
01:15:03,805 --> 01:15:05,528
What's next?

1072
01:15:05,552 --> 01:15:08,453
- I went back to the lab afterwards.
- Did anyone see her?

1073
01:15:08,477 --> 01:15:12,015
No, the lab assistant
finished work at 6 p.m.

1074
01:15:12,040 --> 01:15:14,941
In short, he has no
alibi between 5 p.m. and 8 p.m.

1075
01:15:15,672 --> 01:15:17,176
Let's continue!

1076
01:15:17,840 --> 01:15:20,815
Since he does not want to help us,
I am obliged despite myself

1077
01:15:20,839 --> 01:15:22,455
To put her under arrest.

1078
01:15:22,480 --> 01:15:23,993
Do you have anything to say?

1079
01:15:25,000 --> 01:15:26,401
Can I notify the dean?

1080
01:15:26,425 --> 01:15:27,425
Here it is.

1081
01:15:39,840 --> 01:15:42,606
Hello. I would like to speak to
Dean Geran, please.

1082
01:15:42,840 --> 01:15:44,195
Yes, who is this?

1083
01:15:44,219 --> 01:15:45,460
Is that you, Edith?

1084
01:15:45,485 --> 01:15:47,013
Yes, where are you, honey?

1085
01:15:47,037 --> 01:15:49,393
I'm not going home tonight.
They arrested me.

1086
01:15:49,560 --> 01:15:51,666
Arrested? Why?

1087
01:15:51,691 --> 01:15:53,826
I am accused of the
disappearance of my assistant.

1088
01:15:53,851 --> 01:15:55,239
Stay where you are. Coming.

1089
01:15:55,263 --> 01:15:58,480
How-what do you mean come? Edith.

1090
01:16:00,940 --> 01:16:05,095
Good morning, Mr. Commissioner.
Edith Geran, the girlfriend.

1091
01:16:05,120 --> 01:16:08,255
Oh, my poor darling.
I did it as fast as I could.

1092
01:16:08,280 --> 01:16:10,317
Oh, very nice! What is it?

1093
01:16:10,480 --> 01:16:12,866
Ashtray.
The murder weapon.

1094
01:16:14,960 --> 01:16:16,598
Fascinating.

1095
01:16:18,240 --> 01:16:20,908
Well, so do I, Commissioner,

1096
01:16:20,932 --> 01:16:24,833
I have something to tell you,
which will thrill you.

1097
01:16:26,200 --> 01:16:29,549
To make a long story short, my darling,
the commissioner accuses you

1098
01:16:29,573 --> 01:16:32,921
Of a childish tryst
between you and your assistant.

1099
01:16:32,946 --> 01:16:34,886
Look, Edith, this is not the time.

1100
01:16:35,326 --> 01:16:38,441
I have come to provide them,
Mr. Commissioner,

1101
01:16:38,466 --> 01:16:43,150
proof that my fiancé is
innocent of the crime he is accused of.

1102
01:16:44,453 --> 01:16:53,796
This is because of a little thing
that can be found here. Here it is.

1103
01:16:55,173 --> 01:16:57,526
Here is the result of
a small survey.

1104
01:16:58,769 --> 01:17:02,870
I like the certainty. I had some
doubts, and I realized that between certainty

1105
01:17:02,894 --> 01:17:06,995
and doubts there is a difference
of 3,000 francs per day.

1106
01:17:07,020 --> 01:17:11,260
Those 3,000 francs demanded
by the agency Eye of the Lynx,

1107
01:17:11,285 --> 01:17:15,637
of your colleagues, Mr.
Commissioner, to supervise someone.

1108
01:17:16,560 --> 01:17:20,355
From 4 p.m. June 25

1109
01:17:20,379 --> 01:17:23,053
the agency Eye of the Lynx
watches over my fiancé.

1110
01:17:24,473 --> 01:17:29,711
From these papers I will read you an
excerpt from their first report.

1111
01:17:29,840 --> 01:17:33,346
On June 25 at 4 p.m., Prof.
Norman was joined

1112
01:17:33,371 --> 01:17:37,479
by our client who met him
met him in the university courtyard.

1113
01:17:37,504 --> 01:17:40,313
After a very brief conversation
with a young blonde woman,

1114
01:17:40,338 --> 01:17:44,116
takes a cab, which takes him
takes him to the research laboratory.

1115
01:17:44,280 --> 01:17:47,148
After realizing that there is no
there is no other way to leave the premises,

1116
01:17:47,172 --> 01:17:49,126
We lurk in front of the door.

1117
01:17:49,151 --> 01:17:54,751
Afterwards, the professor leaves to go to
his house, where he stays all evening.

1118
01:17:54,776 --> 01:17:56,697
The reading of these
documents is tedious.

1119
01:17:56,721 --> 01:17:58,537
You can read them yourself,
commissioner.

1120
01:17:58,562 --> 01:18:02,250
He will observe that as of
4 p.m. June 25,

1121
01:18:02,275 --> 01:18:05,495
When Miss, what's her name,
Monette was still alive,

1122
01:18:05,520 --> 01:18:07,510
My fiancé never saw her again.

1123
01:18:07,535 --> 01:18:11,714
Consequently, he did not rape her,
did not kidnap her, did not kill her.

1124
01:18:11,739 --> 01:18:12,739
That's it.

1125
01:18:14,420 --> 01:18:17,875
Commissioner, we found
a rhinoceros in the old harbor!

1126
01:18:18,133 --> 01:18:20,405
How did you know
that June 26 was

1127
01:18:20,429 --> 01:18:22,701
the day of my last
meeting with Monette?

1128
01:18:22,726 --> 01:18:25,375
Because the report mentioned it.

1129
01:18:25,400 --> 01:18:28,806
And did you continue to spy on me, knowing
That I had never seen you again?

1130
01:18:28,945 --> 01:18:31,465
I was too amused
to read that you visited

1131
01:18:31,490 --> 01:18:34,344
the police station,
the lost and found, the antique dealer!

1132
01:18:35,647 --> 01:18:37,046
Perfect!

1133
01:18:38,299 --> 01:18:41,417
Is this your thanks
For getting you out of prison!

1134
01:18:50,680 --> 01:18:54,196
I was wondering how long it would take you
to think about the ads.

1135
01:18:54,360 --> 01:18:57,921
"Big reward to the person who finds
the figurine of a naked woman..."

1136
01:18:57,946 --> 01:18:59,507
Then do you know?

1137
01:18:59,532 --> 01:19:02,175
Honey, you have no secrets from me.

1138
01:19:02,200 --> 01:19:05,511
I should have figured it out.
You were the one who took it.

1139
01:19:05,680 --> 01:19:07,079
Where is it!

1140
01:19:07,433 --> 01:19:09,002
Let go of me! You're hurting me!

1141
01:19:09,027 --> 01:19:10,027
Where is it?

1142
01:19:10,052 --> 01:19:11,238
I took it to the bank!

1143
01:19:11,838 --> 01:19:13,565
Then let's go there now! Now!

1144
01:19:13,590 --> 01:19:16,615
It is too late. The banks are
already closed. And listen carefully...

1145
01:19:16,640 --> 01:19:20,606
I will never give you back that
statuette. Do you hear me? Never!

1146
01:19:20,800 --> 01:19:22,595
You are committing a crime.

1147
01:19:22,619 --> 01:19:24,077
Oh, yeah? And where is the body?

1148
01:19:24,240 --> 01:19:26,035
You are stealing a girl's life!

1149
01:19:26,059 --> 01:19:27,790
She stole my fiancé!

1150
01:19:28,020 --> 01:19:31,046
I will give her back her life when
I get my fiancé back.

1151
01:19:34,873 --> 01:19:38,873
Ah, all right...
Come on, dictate your terms.

1152
01:19:39,760 --> 01:19:43,527
First, we will get away
from this little charmer.

1153
01:19:43,552 --> 01:19:46,435
Anne-lise and her husband invited us
to spend the vacations in America.

1154
01:19:46,460 --> 01:19:47,460
And what are we going to do there?

1155
01:19:47,485 --> 01:19:48,626
We are going to get married.

1156
01:19:48,960 --> 01:19:51,115
On our return,
we will move to Paris.

1157
01:19:51,139 --> 01:19:52,794
How, and why?

1158
01:19:52,960 --> 01:19:57,557
We will work together at Juvacola.
I will become an advertising executive.

1159
01:19:57,840 --> 01:20:00,480
After one year, hopefully,

1160
01:20:00,599 --> 01:20:04,558
I will send the figurine to mom with
your CPR instructions.

1161
01:20:06,120 --> 01:20:08,555
And... what if I refuse?

1162
01:20:09,460 --> 01:20:12,612
I am the mistress of the situation.
In that case, I would leave.

1163
01:20:12,720 --> 01:20:15,360
And your figurine...

1164
01:20:18,160 --> 01:20:21,352
Good. I accept.

1165
01:20:21,377 --> 01:20:24,477
Here it is...
I finally recognize you.

1166
01:20:24,502 --> 01:20:27,837
This girl has had
a hateful influence on you.

1167
01:20:29,080 --> 01:20:32,615
You know, I was so sure
to bring you back into the fold

1168
01:20:32,640 --> 01:20:34,846
that I have prepared a
bottle of champagne.

1169
01:20:37,240 --> 01:20:39,470
I am glad that
you said yes.

1170
01:20:40,320 --> 01:20:43,836
It would have been very unpleasant to do
what I had decided to do.

1171
01:20:44,613 --> 01:20:46,047
What had you decided?

1172
01:20:46,072 --> 01:20:48,767
The moment my
ship had left port,

1173
01:20:48,791 --> 01:20:51,053
I would have thrown the figurine into the sea.

1174
01:20:51,077 --> 01:20:52,514
To us!

1175
01:21:10,086 --> 01:21:14,695
1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8, 9...

1176
01:21:14,720 --> 01:21:15,835
Where are the others?

1177
01:21:15,859 --> 01:21:17,314
What others?

1178
01:21:17,480 --> 01:21:19,666
Two dark bags
and the three black suitcases.

1179
01:21:19,691 --> 01:21:23,932
The gentleman's? The gentleman
took them back five minutes ago.

1180
01:21:23,957 --> 01:21:25,108
Isn't he going with you?

1181
01:21:25,132 --> 01:21:27,231
It is not possible!

1182
01:21:27,256 --> 01:21:28,505
Do you have my bag, Mom?

1183
01:21:28,529 --> 01:21:30,152
Yes, but I don't understand it.

1184
01:21:30,177 --> 01:21:31,557
You don't have to understand.

1185
01:21:31,582 --> 01:21:35,273
If Jerome wants to take it from you, don't
let him do so for any reason.

1186
01:21:38,593 --> 01:21:39,595
Ah...

1187
01:21:39,619 --> 01:21:41,448
I'm not leaving.
I have changed my mind.

1188
01:21:41,473 --> 01:21:45,055
But my dear, everything has been arranged
For your departure. You are expected!

1189
01:21:45,080 --> 01:21:46,652
And then you signed a contract.

1190
01:21:46,677 --> 01:21:48,914
Edith did it.
She signed the contract.

1191
01:21:49,080 --> 01:21:54,168
My husband will sue you! You have
making fun of us! Raymond! Raymond!

1192
01:21:54,193 --> 01:21:57,808
Do you know what you are doing? As soon as we
we set sail, the statuette will go overboard.

1193
01:21:57,833 --> 01:21:59,575
I don't like to travel.

1194
01:21:59,600 --> 01:22:04,312
And you won't, you wouldn't dare to throw it
Into this terrible salt sea.

1195
01:22:04,337 --> 01:22:06,143
We shall see!

1196
01:22:06,168 --> 01:22:07,445
I bet not.

1197
01:22:07,470 --> 01:22:08,952
And I bet it does.

1198
01:22:08,976 --> 01:22:10,015
You break my heart.

1199
01:22:10,040 --> 01:22:11,649
I love to do that.

1200
01:22:11,673 --> 01:22:14,091
Edith, give it back to me.

1201
01:22:14,116 --> 01:22:15,274
No!

1202
01:22:16,069 --> 01:22:19,704
Don't you have anything else to say?
Have you thought it through?

1203
01:22:20,689 --> 01:22:22,049
Perfect!

1204
01:22:22,640 --> 01:22:23,869
My bag...

1205
01:22:37,333 --> 01:22:38,846
Haven't you changed your mind?

1206
01:22:54,680 --> 01:22:56,255
Quick! Follow that ship!

1207
01:22:56,280 --> 01:22:57,688
But he goes to America.

1208
01:22:57,713 --> 01:22:59,318
I'll stop you first.

1209
01:23:10,400 --> 01:23:12,059
Drop it!

1210
01:23:16,640 --> 01:23:19,146
Let it fall! Let it fall! Let it fall!

1211
01:23:25,760 --> 01:23:27,512
Allow me, miss!

1212
01:23:27,680 --> 01:23:33,295
Thank you. But aren't you Alberic
Cahuzac? But yes, I recognize her!

1213
01:23:33,320 --> 01:23:35,121
Oh, you were at my conference?

1214
01:23:35,146 --> 01:23:38,466
Of course. I subscribe to all
Alliance Française events.

1215
01:23:38,886 --> 01:23:40,721
Aren't we going too far?

1216
01:23:40,745 --> 01:23:42,767
Go ahead. I will give you double.

1217
01:23:42,792 --> 01:23:45,527
I was afraid that the topic
was a little difficult

1218
01:23:45,551 --> 01:23:47,912
for ears
so fascinating.

1219
01:23:48,560 --> 01:23:49,721
But no!

1220
01:23:49,745 --> 01:23:52,438
"The influence of epic myth
on Roman literature."

1221
01:23:52,463 --> 01:23:53,772
Nothing more interesting.

1222
01:23:53,797 --> 01:23:55,591
But what does it do!

1223
01:23:55,800 --> 01:23:57,551
Faster! Faster!

1224
01:23:57,576 --> 01:24:00,722
Hey, hey, if we continue,
I will break my engine.

1225
01:24:00,747 --> 01:24:04,582
Will you allow me to look at it?
It is a lovely object.

1226
01:24:05,880 --> 01:24:08,474
One could fall in love
with this little object.

1227
01:24:08,640 --> 01:24:10,335
No, no, it's not a big deal.

1228
01:24:10,359 --> 01:24:11,973
Wait, wait...

1229
01:24:11,998 --> 01:24:13,673
- Oh no!
- I am desolated!

1230
01:24:15,380 --> 01:24:16,461
Finally!

1231
01:24:16,485 --> 01:24:18,735
Do you often schedule
appointments on the high seas?

1232
01:24:18,760 --> 01:24:20,717
This is the first and last time.

